English: (A case requesting a guide for a culinary tour?)
German:
(Ein Fall, für den ein Fremdenführer für eine
Restauranttour gesucht wird?)

English:
(I guess some people are completely unfazed by
everything that's been going on lately.)
Chinese:
（明明到處都陷入很糟糕的狀況，
　還有這種很樂天的人啊）
Korean:
(여기저기 대소동이 벌어지고 있는데
 한가로운 사람이 다 있군)
German:
(Ich schätze, einige Leute haben die Vorfälle
der letzten Zeit völlig kalt gelassen.)

English:
(But it might be good to do stuff like this from
time to time. The client is waiting in Shibuya.)
Chinese:
（但是，偶爾這樣子或許還不錯。
　委託人似乎在涉谷等著。先過去看看吧）
Korean:
(하지만 가끔 이런 것도 좋을지도 몰라.
 의뢰인은 시부야에서 기다리고 있는 모양이다. 가보자)
German:
(Aber es ist vielleicht nicht schlecht, ab und zu
so was zu machen. Der Klient wartet in Shibuya.)
